{"title_page": "Mariacarla Boscono", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian fashion model|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=December 2008}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Mariacarla Boscono\n| image        = Mariacarla Boscono.jpg\n| caption      = Mariacarla Boscono, September 2009\n| imagesize    =\n| birth_name   = Mariacarla Boscono\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1980|9|20}}\n| birth_place  = [[Rome]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| nationality  = Italian\n| height       = {{height|m=1.78|precision=0}}\n| haircolor    = Black\n| eyecolor     = Brown\n| agency       = [[Women Management]] (worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/mariacarla-boscono|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Model|publisher=}}</ref>\n| website      =\n| children     = 1\n}}\n'''Mariacarla Boscono''' ({{IPA-it|ma\u02ccri.a\u02c8karla bo\u02c8sk\u0254\u02d0no|pron}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comesipronuncia.it/pronuncia/mariacarla-boscono-2133|title=Come si pronuncia Mariacarla Boscono|work=comesipronuncia.it|lang=it|accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref> born 20 September 1980) is an [[Italians|Italian]] [[Model (person)|Top model]] and [[actress]]. Rose in fame in lately [[90s]], Boscono walks the runway of mayors worldwide [[Fashion week|fashion weeks]] and [[Festival|festivals]], including [[Milan Fashion Week]], [[New York Fashion Week]] and [[Paris Fashion Week]] , the [[Met Gala]] and [[Venice Film Festival]]. In 2005, in two weeks, she walked more than seventy runway in three different cities ([[Milan]], [[New York City]], [[Paris]]), establishing a world record.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.luisaviaroma.com/en-us/crrunway/mariacarla-boscono-on-being-fashions-beauty-chameleon|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Record|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n''[[Vogue Paris]]'' declared her one of the top 30 models of the 2000s and in 2005 she earned an estimated $3,500,000 in the past 12 months for a spot on ''[[Forbes]]''' list of the ''World's 15 Top-Earning Supermodels'' .<ref>[http://www.vogue.fr/mode/en_vogue/091218-les-mannequins-des-annees-2000.aspx Les 30 Mannequins des Ann\u00e9es 2000] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/66nvf6dic?url=http://www.vogue.fr/mode/en-vogue/diaporama/les-30-mannequins-des-annees-2000/1662 |date=9 April 2012 }} Retrieved 2010-01-20</ref> The model.com website includes it in the ''Icons List'', the ranking of the twenty supermodels considered icons in the fashion industry.<ref name=\"models.com\">[http://models.com/models/mariacarla-boscono Mariacarla Boscono \u2013 Models.com]</ref>\n\nBoscono has worked with the most recognized fashion brands and she became one of the favorite model of [[Karl Lagerfeld]] and the muse of [[Riccardo Tisci]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/met-gala-2019-mariacarla-boscono-camp-burberry-riccardo-tisci|title=Met Gala 2019: Mariacarla Boscono incarna il Camp indossando Burberry|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>. She has posed for major fashion magazines, photographed by [[Juergen Teller]], [[Steven Meisel]], [[Tim Walker]], [[Peter Lindbergh]], [[Peter Beard]] and [[Mert and Marcus]]. Boscono also worked with other [[Model (person)|Top model]] like [[Natalia Vodianova]], [[Caroline Trentini]], [[Karlie Kloss]], [[Naomi Campbell]], and [[Joan Smalls]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iodonna.it/personaggi/interviste-gallery/2017/10/05/mariacarla-boscono-festeggia-20-anni-di-carriera/|title=Mariacarla Boscono festeggia 20 anni di carriera|last=Villa|first=Martina|date=2017-10-05|website=iO Donna|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nBoscono has her theatrical debut in 2006 in [[New York City|New York]] with the play ''The Maids'' by [[Jean Genet]] and between 2010-2011 in Imogen Kusch's plays ''Shakespeare's Women, The Winter's Tale'' and ''[[Cymbeline]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://the-style-post.blogspot.com/2011/02/mariacarla-boscono-all-for-shakespeare.html|title=The Style Post: Mariacarla Boscono, \"I'm all for Shakespeare '|last=G|first=Ernesto|date=2011-02-19|website=The Style Post|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nShe including [[Chanel]], [[Blumarine]], [[Moschino]], [[Etro]], [[Givenchy]], [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]], [[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]], [[Escada]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[DKNY]], [[Diesel S.p.A.|Diesel]], [[Roberto Cavalli]], [[Alberta Ferretti]], [[Armani Exchange|Armani]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Barneys New York]], [[NARS Cosmetics]], [[H&M]], [[John Galliano]], [[Hermes]], [[Lanvin (clothing)|Lanvin]], [[Loewe, S.A.|Loewe]], [[Prada]], [[Pucci]], [[Missoni]], [[Laura Biagiotti]] and [[Salvatore Ferragamo]].\n\n== Early life ==\nBoscono was born in [[Rome]], Italy. She spent most of her early life travelling because of her father's work. Her parents lived in Thailand before she was born, but after her mother became pregnant they moved back to Italy. She spent a couple of years there until moving to [[Providence, Rhode Island]] and then [[Key West]], Florida. She spent her early school years in the United States, but her parents thought it would be better for Boscono to study in Italy and reconnect with her Italian heritage. This did not last very long though: at 9 years old Boscono and her family moved to Kenya, living in a village between [[Malindi]] and [[Mombasa]]. Boscono described her years in Kenya as \"the most fantastic in her life\".\n\n== Modeling career ==\nBoscono was discovered at 17, during a dinner with a family friend who happened to be a photographer. The friend and Boscono's mother encouraged her to begin a modeling career, but Boscono chose to finish school first. Soon after graduating high school she flew to New York City, signed with DNA Model Management. Her first runways were in 1997 for [[Laura Biagiotti]] and [[Alberta Ferretti]], continuingn later [[90s]] for italian and international stylists like Gai Mattiolo, [[Rocco Barocco]], [[Fausto Sarli]], [[Paul Smith (fashion designer)|Paul Smith]], [[Issey Miyake]], [[Vivienne Westwood]], [[Guy Laroche]]. Boscono was noted by [[Karl Lagerfeld]], becoming one of the favourite models of the stylist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iodonna.it/personaggi/interviste-gallery/2017/10/05/mariacarla-boscono-festeggia-20-anni-di-carriera/|title=Mariacarla Boscono festeggia 20 anni di carriera|last=Villa|first=Martina|date=2017-10-05|website=iO Donna|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> It did not take long for Boscono to rise as an internationally known model, being featured on the cover of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' several times and walking in many high fashion runway shows of the first years of [[00s (decade)|00s]] for [[Armani Exchange|Armani]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Escada]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]], [[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]] [[Michael Kors]] and [[Alberta Ferretti]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://models.com/work/armani-exchange-armani-exchange-fw-2001|title=Armani Exchange F/W 2001 (Armani Exchange)|website=MODELS.com|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://italian-models.blogspot.com/2012/04/escada-spring-2003-mariacarla-karen-and.html|title=Modelle Italiane,: Escada Spring 2003: Mariacarla, Karen and Liya by Steven Meisel|last=Milena|date=2012-04-15|website=Modelle Italiane,|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gettyimages.it/detail/fotografie-di-cronaca/mariacarla-boscono-attends-michael-kors-fashion-fotografie-di-cronaca/658735312|title=Mariacarla Boscono attends Michael Kors fashion show at the tents...|website=Getty Images|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\nDuring the 2005 season, Boscono walked in over seventy fashion shows between [[New York City]], [[Milan]] and [[Paris]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnaglamour.it/chi-e-mariacarla-boscono-altezza-eta-e-curiosita-sulla-modella/curiosita/|title=Mariacarla Boscono: dalla conquista delle passerelle, alla storia con Ghali|date=2020-02-05|website=Donna Glamour|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> She was named spokesperson for [[H&M]] in 2005, replacing [[Kate Moss]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> and during 2006's Fall Fashion Week she traded in her long dark locks for a short platinum blonde hairstyle reminiscent of [[Jean Seberg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alamy.it/foto-immagine-modello-mariacarla-boscono-molto-breve-capelli-biondi-indossa-oro-minidress-sequinned-slash-il-collo-e-la-prua-su-un-lato-le-paillettes-43820434.html|title=Modello Mariacarla Boscono molto breve capelli biondi indossa oro minidress sequinned slash il collo e la prua su un lato le paillettes Foto & Immagine Stock: 43820434|last=Limited|first=Alamy|website=Alamy|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Boscono was absent from the runways for both the Fall/Winter 2007 and Spring/Summer 2007 seasons. {{As of|2008}}, Boscono made her return to the runways in Paris at the Fall/Winter 2008 Couture collection for [[Dior]] and she was the sole face of [[Emilio Pucci]], [[Herm\u00e8s]], [[John Galliano]], and [[Moschino]] ad campaigns and walked for brands like [[Gucci]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Fendi]], [[Versace]], [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], and [[Jean Paul Gaultier]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lei.excite.it/foto/dolce-gabbana-springsummer-2009-la-campagna-P8082-0-dolce-gabbana-campagna-primavera-estate-2009.html|title=Dolce & Gabbana Spring/Summer 2009: la campagna|website=Excite|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In November 2008, she signed a contract for the new Moschino's fragrance \"Glamour\", photographed by [[Patrick Demarchelier]] and she becomes the new face of the Dolce & Gabbana Spring/Summer 2009 advertising campaign with Brazilian model [[Caroline Trentini]] and American model [[Karlie Kloss]]. She posed in Africa for the 2009 [[Pirelli Calendar]] by [[Peter Beard]]. In 2009, she became the face of [[Dolce & Gabbana]] and Givenchy Spring/Summer 2009 ad campaigns. She was the face of the Fall/Winter 2009 [[Salvatore Ferragamo]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]] and Dolce & Gabbana ad campaigns.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n\nIn 2011 she was photographed by [[Steven Meisel]] for [[Prada]]'s spring collection and returned to fashion shows for [[Roberto Cavalli]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.paperblog.com/mariacarla-boscono-x-roberto-cavalli-inverno-2012-la-campagna-472592/|title=Mariacarla Boscono X Roberto Cavalli Inverno 2012 \u2013 La Campagna|website=Paperblog|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.italianstylekuwait.com/2010/11/mariacarla-boscono-by-steven-meisel/|title=Italian Style in Kuwait {{!}} Mariacarla Boscono by Steven Meisel|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In the same year she became the testimonial of [[Givenchy]]'s \"Dahlia Noir\" perfume.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.grazia.it/bellezza/profumi/givenchy-dahlia-noir|title=Givenchy Dahlia Noir: il nuovo profumo haute couture - Grazia.it|date=2012-09-03|website=Grazia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Boscono was also invited with [[Riccardo Tisci]] at [[Met Gala]]. In 2012 she is called for [[Missoni]]'s spring campaign,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://r1ma.blogspot.com/2012/04/mariacarla-boscono-for-missoni-spring.html|title=\u2665\u2665\u2665 Mariacarla Boscono for Missoni Spring 2012 full Ad Campaign by Juergen Teller|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> while in 2013 she walked in [[Armani]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.fashionnetwork.com/news/Mariacarla-boscono-nella-nuova-campagna-giorgio-armani,334531.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono nella nuova campagna Giorgio Armani|last=IT|first=FashionNetwork com|website=FashionNetwork.com|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> [[Alberta Ferretti]] and [[Dior]]'s runways.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashiontimes.it/2013/07/mariacarla-boscono-per-alberta-ferretti/|title=Mariacarla Boscono per Alberta Ferretti|date=2013-07-09|website=Fashion Times|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashionblog.it/post/114967/dior-presenta-la-nuova-collezione-autunno-inverno-2013-2014|title=Dior presenta la nuova collezione autunno-inverno 2013-2014|date=2013-07-26|website=Fashionblog.it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> From 2014 to 2015 she became the new model for [[Salvatore Ferragamo]] and came back to [[Alberta Ferretti]]'s runway. In 2014 she was photographed by [[Mert and Marcus]] for spring session by [[Armani]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.fashionnetwork.com/news/Mariacarla-boscono-nella-nuova-campagna-giorgio-armani,334531.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono nella nuova campagna Giorgio Armani|last=IT|first=FashionNetwork com|website=FashionNetwork.com|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 Boscono is hired for the Fall/Winter collection for [[Chanel]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chanel.com/it_IT/moda/news/2016/07/fall-winter-2016-17-pre-collection.html|title=PRE-COLLEZIONE AUTUNNO-INVERNO 2016/17|last=CHANEL|website=CHANEL|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[Mugler]] and spring campaign of [[Stella McCartney]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilgazzettino.it/moda/stella_mccartney_sceglie_natalia_vodianova_mariacarla_boscono_estate_2016-1580865.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono new entry per Stella McCartney|website=www.ilgazzettino.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fashioneditorials.com/mariacarla-boscono-and-natasha-poly-by-mert-alas-marcus-piggott/|title=LA PERLA S/S 2016 - Mariacarla Boscono and Natasha Poly by Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott|date=2016-01-06|website=Fashion Editorials|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> and [[Redken]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/beauty-features/redken-mariacarla-boscono-new-face-10338416/|title=Redken Taps Mariacarla Boscono|last=Weil|first=Jennifer|last2=Weil|first2=Jennifer|date=2016-02-03|website=WWD|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2017 she becomes the face of [[Bottega Veneta]], [[Vera Wang]] and [[Oscar de la Renta]]'s Fall/Winter campaigns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwebradio.fm/oscar-de-la-renta-sara-mariacarla-boscono-il-volto-della-campagna-autunno-inverno-2017-2018/|title=Oscar de la Renta: sar\u00e0 Mariacarla Boscono il volto della campagna autunno inverno 2017-2018|date=2017-08-24|website=iWebRadio - Emozioni Senza Confini !!!|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2018 she appeared in [[Equipment (clothing brand)|Equipment]] collection,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voila.life/moda/mariacarla-boscono-2018-equipment/|title=Mariacarla Boscono \u00e8 protagonista della campagna 2018 di Equipment|last=Chimera|first=Patrizia|date=2018-02-27|website=Voil\u00e0 Magazine|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[Ermanno Scervino]] winter collection photographed by [[Peter Lindbergh]], and the new luxury collection by [[Marc Jacobs]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/foto-gallery/moda/news/17_giugno_09/ermanno-scervino-profumo-donna-mariacarla-boscono-cara-delevingne-brigitte-macron-2350f7c8-4d18-11e7-a0c3-52aebd58a53d.shtml|title=Ermanno Scervino, profumo di donna tra Mariacarla Boscono, Cara Delevingne e Brigitte Macron|date=2017-09-06|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/it/star/a25785299/mariacarla-boscono-chi-e-modella-italiana/|title=Mariacarla Boscono, la top model magnetica che ama il no-underwear e la perdita di controllo|last=Adorno|first=Di Mary|date=2019-01-08|website=Cosmopolitan|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2019 [[Paris Fashion Week]] she walks on chat-way for [[Valentino (fashion designer)|Valentino]] and she was the guest model for [[Karl Lagerfeld]]<nowiki/>x[[Luisa Via Roma|LuisaViaRoma]]'s for the 90\u00b0 anniversary of the boutique.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amica.it/gallery/luisaviaroma-la-sfilata-evento-per-90-anni-della-boutique/?item=86|title=LuisaViaRoma: la sfilata-evento per i 90 anni della boutique Foto 86|website=Amica|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zimbio.com/photos/Mariacarla+Boscono/Valentino+Runway+Paris+Fashion+Week+Haute/EORInagUc6x|title=Mariacarla Boscono Photos Photos: Valentino : Runway - Paris Fashion Week - Haute Couture Fall/Winter 2019/2020|website=Zimbio|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Boscono mada a campaign for [[Burberry]] in [[Korea]] and participated at [[Met Gala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/editorial/mariacarla-boscono-burberry-vogue-korea-cover/|title=Mariacarla Boscono Charms in Burberry for Vogue Korea|date=2019-01-28|website=Fashion Gone Rogue|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/met-gala-2019-mariacarla-boscono-camp-burberry-riccardo-tisci|title=Met Gala 2019: Mariacarla Boscono incarna il Camp indossando Burberry|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In 2020 she is the new face for [[Zara (retailer)|Zara]]'s summer collection,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/gallery/zara-campagna-primavera-estate-2020-mariacarla-boscono|title=Zara: Mariacarla Boscono testimonial della knitwear primavera estate 2020|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> the model for [[Daniel Lee (designer)|Daniel Lee]]'s collection for [[Bottega Veneta]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mffashion.com/news/backstage/daniel-lee-presenta-la-nuova-collezione-di-bottega-veneta-201906131227048464|title=Daniel Lee's collection 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> she walks the runway of [[Tod's]], [[Versace]], [[Burberry]], [[Salvatore Ferragamo]], [[Tom Ford]] Fall/Winter collections. Boscono walked also [[Valentino (fashion designer)|Valentino]]'s runway and posed for his spring campaign by [[Juergen Teller]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zimbio.com/photos/Mariacarla+Boscono/Tod+Runway+Milan+Fashion+Week+Fall+Winter/hfsbCtQYNAX|title=Mariacarla Boscono Photos Photos: Tod's - Runway - Milan Fashion Week Fall/Winter 2020-2021|website=Zimbio|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n== Theatre career ==\nOn 18 May 2006, Boscono made her theater debut as Solange in [[Jean Genet]]'s ''The Maids'' at the [[Lee Strasberg]] Theatre Institute in New York. [[Margherita Missoni]] played the role of her sister.<ref>{{cite journal|journal=The Daily Mini|last=Krentcil|first=Faran|title=Maid of Honor|date=July 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/fashion/models/mboscono/mariacarlaboscono/|website=New York Magazine|accessdate=23 August 2014|title=Model Profile \u2013 Mariacarla Boscono}}</ref> In 2010she played the role of Florizer in Imogen Kusch's ''Shakespeare's Women'' at [[Colosseum]] in [[Rome]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> while in 2011 she acted in ''The Winter's Tale'' and ''[[Cymbeline]]'', both by Imogen Kusch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.klesidra.org/project/king-cymbeline/|title=King Cymbeline \u2013 Klesidra|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://the-style-post.blogspot.com/2011/02/mariacarla-boscono-all-for-shakespeare.html|title=The Style Post: Mariacarla Boscono, \"I'm all for Shakespeare '|last=G|first=Ernesto|date=2011-02-19|website=The Style Post|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn August 2012, Mariacarla announced the birth of her daughter, Marialucas.<ref>Alex Rees, [http://nymag.com/thecut/2012/08/mariacarla-boscono-gave-birth.html# And Just Like That, Mariacarla Boscono Gave Birth\"], ''New York Magazine'', August 2012</ref> She is a single mother.<ref>Faran Krentcil, [http://www.elle.com/fashion/interviews/a32452/mariacarla-boscono-interview/ \"Mariacarla Boscono on Modeling, Motherhood and Mac n' Cheese\"], ''Elle'', December 2015</ref> Boscono is living in New York, and calls it her second home, coming second after her birthplace of Rome.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n\nSince 2019 she is into a relationshio with tirteen younger italian rapper [[Ghali (rapper)|Ghali]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/sette/incontri/20_febbraio_14/ghali-ecco-chi-sono-io-radici-arabe-italiane-milano-mia-casa-fdaf7756-4b6b-11ea-aff7-4a3600894a18.shtml|title=Ghali: \"Fino all\u2019anno scorso dormivo con mamma. Mariacarla? Mi ama anche se la carriera finisce\"|last=Proietti|first=Andrea Laffranchi e Michela|date=2020-02-14|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\n== Agencies ==\n* Women New York\n* Women Milan (Mother Agency)\n* Women Paris<ref>[http://www.womenmanagement.fr/model/2563/mariacarla-boscono/''Women Paris'']</ref>\n\n== Clothing brands and magazine covers ==\n\n=== Clothing brands ===\n\n* [[Alberta Ferretti]] (1997-2000, 2013-2015)\n*[[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]] (1998-2001)\n*[[Armani]] (2000-2001, 2013-2015)\n* [[Bottega Veneta]] (2017-present)\n*[[Bulgari]] (2010\n*[[Burberry]] (2019-present)\n*[[Calvin Klein (company)|Calvin Klein]] (2000-2003)\n*[[Chanel]] (1997-present)\n* Coccinelle<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyonline.it/it/2016/coccinelle-va-online-con-la-top-mariacarla-boscono-per-la-collezione-pe|title=Coccinelle va online con la top Mariacarla Boscono per la collezione P/E|website=www.dailyonline.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> (2016)\n*[[Comme des Gar\u00e7ons]] (1999-2000)\n* [[Dior]] (2008-2009, 2013-2014)\n* [[Dolce & Gabbana]] (2000-2009)\n* [[DSquared2]] (2016-present)\n* [[Emilio Pucci]] (2008)\n*[[Equipment (clothing brand)|Equipment]] (2018)\n*[[Ermanno Scervino]] (2017-2018)\n*[[Escada]] (2003-2004)\n*[[Fausto Sarli]] (1997-2000)\n* [[Fendi]] (2008)\n*Gai Mattiolo (1997-1998)\n*[[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]] (2000-2009)\n*[[Givenchy]] (2000-present)\n* [[Gucci]] (2008, 2016)\n*[[Guy Laroche]] (1997-present)\n*[[H&M]] (2005-2006)\n* [[Herm\u00e8s]] (2008)\n*[[Issey Miyake]] (1997)\n* [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]] (2008)\n* [[John Galliano]] (2008)\n* [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]] (2015-2016)\n*[[Lanvin (company)|Lanvin]] (2010)\n*[[Laura Biagiotti]] (1997-1998)\n*[[Karl Lagerfeld]] (1997-present)\n*[[Marc Jacobs]] (2018)\n*[[Michael Kors]] (2003-2004)\n*[[Missoni]] (2012)\n* [[Moschino]] (2008)\n* [[Thierry Mugler|Mugler]] (2016)\n* [[NARS Cosmetics]] (2016)\n*[[Off-White (company)|Off-White]] (2019-2020)\n* [[Oscar de la Renta]] (2017)\n*[[Paul Smith (fashion designer)|Paul Smith]] (1997)\n*[[Prada]] (2011)\n*[[Proenza Schouler]] (2018)\n* [[Redken]] (2016)\n* [[Rag & Bone]] (2016-2017)\n*[[Roberto Cavalli]] (2010-2012)\n*[[Rocco Barocco]] (1997-1998)\n*[[Salvatore Ferragamo]] (2009, 2014-2015, 2019-2020)\n* [[Sportmax]] (2016)\n* [[Stella McCartney]] (2016)\n* [[Tod's]] (2020)\n*[[Tom Ford]] (2019-2020)\n*[[Valentino (fashion designer)|Valentino]] (2018-present)\n* [[Vera Wang]] (2017)\n* [[Versace]] (2000-present)\n*[[Vivienne Westwood]] (1997)\n* [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]] (2008)\n* [[Zara (retailer)|Zara]] (2020)\n\n=== Magazine ===\n\n* [[Harper's Bazaar|Bazaar -US]]\n* [[Harper's Bazaar|Bazaar - UK]]\n*[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]\n*[[Dazed (magazine)|Dazed]]\n*[[Exit (magazine)|Exit]]\n*[[Elle (magazine)|Elle - Italy]]\n*[[Elle (magazine)|Elle - US]]\n*[[Madame Figaro]]\n*[[Gioia (magazine)|Gioia]]\n* [[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]\n* [[Grazia|Grazia - Italy]]\n*[[IO Donna]]\n*[[Muse Magazine]]\n*[[Num\u00e9ro]]\n*[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]\n* [[Style: (magazine)|Style]]\n*[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]\n* [[Vogue Australia|Vogue - Australia]]\n*[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue - Brasil]]\n*[[Vogue China|Vogue - China]]\n*[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue - Germany]]\n*[[Vogue Italia|Vogue - Italy]]\n*[[Vogue Japan|Vogue - Japan]]\n*[[Vogue Korea|Vogue - Korea]]\n*[[Vogue Paris|Vogue - Paris]]\n*[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue - Russia]]\n*[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue - Turkey]]\n* [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue - US]]\n*[[W (magazine)|W Magazine]]\n*[[032c]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Fashionmodel}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boscono, Mariacarla}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian female models]]\n[[Category:People from Rome]]\n[[Category:Italian emigrants to Kenya]]\n[[Category:Women Management models]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian fashion model|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=December 2008}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Mariacarla Boscono\n| image        = Mariacarla Boscono.jpg\n| caption      = Mariacarla Boscono, September 2009\n| imagesize    =\n| birth_name   = Mariacarla Boscono\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1980|9|20}}\n| birth_place  = [[Rome]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| nationality  = Italian\n| height       = {{height|m=1.78|precision=0}}\n| haircolor    = Black\n| eyecolor     = Brown\n| agency       = [[Women Management]] (worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/mariacarla-boscono|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Model|publisher=}}</ref>\n| website      =\n| children     = 1\n}}\n'''Mariacarla Boscono''' ({{IPA-it|ma\u02ccri.a\u02c8karla bo\u02c8sk\u0254\u02d0no|pron}};<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comesipronuncia.it/pronuncia/mariacarla-boscono-2133|title=Come si pronuncia Mariacarla Boscono|work=comesipronuncia.it|lang=it|accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref> born 20 September 1980) is an [[Italians|Italian]] [[Model (person)|Top model]] and [[actress]]. Rose in fame in lately [[90s]], Boscono walks the runway of mayors worldwide [[Fashion week|fashion weeks]] and [[Festival|festivals]], including [[Milan Fashion Week]], [[New York Fashion Week]] and [[Paris Fashion Week]] , the [[Met Gala]] and [[Venice Film Festival]]. In 2005, in two weeks, she walked more than seventy runway in three different cities ([[Milan]], [[New York City]], [[Paris]]), establishing a world record.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.luisaviaroma.com/en-us/crrunway/mariacarla-boscono-on-being-fashions-beauty-chameleon|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Record|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n\n''[[Vogue Paris]]'' declared her one of the top 30 models of the 2000s and in 2005 she earned an estimated $3,500,000 in the past 12 months for a spot on ''[[Forbes]]''' list of the ''World's 15 Top-Earning Supermodels'' .<ref>[http://www.vogue.fr/mode/en_vogue/091218-les-mannequins-des-annees-2000.aspx Les 30 Mannequins des Ann\u00e9es 2000] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/66nvf6dic?url=http://www.vogue.fr/mode/en-vogue/diaporama/les-30-mannequins-des-annees-2000/1662 |date=9 April 2012 }} Retrieved 2010-01-20</ref> The model.com website includes it in the ''Icons List'', the ranking of the twenty supermodels considered icons in the fashion industry.<ref name=\"models.com\">[http://models.com/models/mariacarla-boscono Mariacarla Boscono \u2013 Models.com]</ref>\n\nBoscono has worked with the most recognized fashion brands and she became one of the favorite model of [[Karl Lagerfeld]] and the muse of [[Riccardo Tisci]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/met-gala-2019-mariacarla-boscono-camp-burberry-riccardo-tisci|title=Met Gala 2019: Mariacarla Boscono incarna il Camp indossando Burberry|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>. She has posed for major fashion magazines, photographed by [[Juergen Teller]], [[Steven Meisel]], [[Tim Walker]], [[Peter Lindbergh]], [[Peter Beard]] and [[Mert and Marcus]]. Boscono also worked with other [[Model (person)|Top model]] like [[Natalia Vodianova]], [[Caroline Trentini]], [[Karlie Kloss]], [[Naomi Campbell]], and [[Joan Smalls]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iodonna.it/personaggi/interviste-gallery/2017/10/05/mariacarla-boscono-festeggia-20-anni-di-carriera/|title=Mariacarla Boscono festeggia 20 anni di carriera|last=Villa|first=Martina|date=2017-10-05|website=iO Donna|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nBoscono has her theatrical debut in 2006 in [[New York City|New York]] with the play ''The Maids'' by [[Jean Genet]] and between 2010-2011 in Imogen Kusch's plays ''Shakespeare's Women, The Winter's Tale'' and ''[[Cymbeline]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://the-style-post.blogspot.com/2011/02/mariacarla-boscono-all-for-shakespeare.html|title=The Style Post: Mariacarla Boscono, \"I'm all for Shakespeare '|last=G|first=Ernesto|date=2011-02-19|website=The Style Post|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nShe including [[Chanel]], [[Blumarine]], [[Moschino]], [[Etro]], [[Givenchy]], [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]], [[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]], [[Escada]], [[Marc Jacobs]], [[DKNY]], [[Diesel S.p.A.|Diesel]], [[Roberto Cavalli]], [[Alberta Ferretti]], [[Armani Exchange|Armani]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Barneys New York]], [[NARS Cosmetics]], [[H&M]], [[John Galliano]], [[Hermes]], [[Lanvin (clothing)|Lanvin]], [[Loewe, S.A.|Loewe]], [[Prada]], [[Pucci]], [[Missoni]], [[Laura Biagiotti]] and [[Salvatore Ferragamo]].\n\n== Early life ==\nBoscono was born in [[Rome]], Italy. She spent most of her early life travelling because of her father's work. Her parents lived in Thailand before she was born, but after her mother became pregnant they moved back to Italy. She spent a couple of years there until moving to [[Providence, Rhode Island]] and then [[Key West]], Florida. She spent her early school years in the United States, but her parents thought it would be better for Boscono to study in Italy and reconnect with her Italian heritage. This did not last very long though: at 9 years old Boscono and her family moved to Kenya, living in a village between [[Malindi]] and [[Mombasa]]. Boscono described her years in Kenya as \"the most fantastic in her life\".\n\n== Modeling career ==\nBoscono was discovered at 17, during a dinner with a family friend who happened to be a photographer. The friend and Boscono's mother encouraged her to begin a modeling career, but Boscono chose to finish school first. Soon after graduating high school she flew to New York City, signed with DNA Model Management. Her first runways were in 1997 for [[Laura Biagiotti]] and [[Alberta Ferretti]], continuingn later [[90s]] for italian and international stylists like Gai Mattiolo, [[Rocco Barocco]], [[Fausto Sarli]], [[Paul Smith (fashion designer)|Paul Smith]], [[Issey Miyake]], [[Vivienne Westwood]], [[Guy Laroche]]. Boscono was noted by [[Karl Lagerfeld]], becoming one of the favourite models of the stylist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iodonna.it/personaggi/interviste-gallery/2017/10/05/mariacarla-boscono-festeggia-20-anni-di-carriera/|title=Mariacarla Boscono festeggia 20 anni di carriera|last=Villa|first=Martina|date=2017-10-05|website=iO Donna|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> It did not take long for Boscono to rise as an internationally known model, being featured on the cover of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' several times and walking in many high fashion runway shows of the first years of [[00s (decade)|00s]] for [[Armani Exchange|Armani]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Escada]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]], [[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]] [[Michael Kors]] and [[Alberta Ferretti]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://models.com/work/armani-exchange-armani-exchange-fw-2001|title=Armani Exchange F/W 2001 (Armani Exchange)|website=MODELS.com|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://italian-models.blogspot.com/2012/04/escada-spring-2003-mariacarla-karen-and.html|title=Modelle Italiane,: Escada Spring 2003: Mariacarla, Karen and Liya by Steven Meisel|last=Milena|date=2012-04-15|website=Modelle Italiane,|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gettyimages.it/detail/fotografie-di-cronaca/mariacarla-boscono-attends-michael-kors-fashion-fotografie-di-cronaca/658735312|title=Mariacarla Boscono attends Michael Kors fashion show at the tents...|website=Getty Images|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\nDuring the 2005 season, Boscono walked in over seventy fashion shows between [[New York City]], [[Milan]] and [[Paris]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnaglamour.it/chi-e-mariacarla-boscono-altezza-eta-e-curiosita-sulla-modella/curiosita/|title=Mariacarla Boscono: dalla conquista delle passerelle, alla storia con Ghali|date=2020-02-05|website=Donna Glamour|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> She was named spokesperson for [[H&M]] in 2005, replacing [[Kate Moss]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> and during 2006's Fall Fashion Week she traded in her long dark locks for a short platinum blonde hairstyle reminiscent of [[Jean Seberg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.alamy.it/foto-immagine-modello-mariacarla-boscono-molto-breve-capelli-biondi-indossa-oro-minidress-sequinned-slash-il-collo-e-la-prua-su-un-lato-le-paillettes-43820434.html|title=Modello Mariacarla Boscono molto breve capelli biondi indossa oro minidress sequinned slash il collo e la prua su un lato le paillettes Foto & Immagine Stock: 43820434|last=Limited|first=Alamy|website=Alamy|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Boscono was absent from the runways for both the Fall/Winter 2007 and Spring/Summer 2007 seasons. {{As of|2008}}, Boscono made her return to the runways in Paris at the Fall/Winter 2008 Couture collection for [[Dior]] and she was the sole face of [[Emilio Pucci]], [[Herm\u00e8s]], [[John Galliano]], and [[Moschino]] ad campaigns and walked for brands like [[Gucci]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Fendi]], [[Versace]], [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], and [[Jean Paul Gaultier]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://lei.excite.it/foto/dolce-gabbana-springsummer-2009-la-campagna-P8082-0-dolce-gabbana-campagna-primavera-estate-2009.html|title=Dolce & Gabbana Spring/Summer 2009: la campagna|website=Excite|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In November 2008, she signed a contract for the new Moschino's fragrance \"Glamour\", photographed by [[Patrick Demarchelier]] and she becomes the new face of the Dolce & Gabbana Spring/Summer 2009 advertising campaign with Brazilian model [[Caroline Trentini]] and American model [[Karlie Kloss]]. She posed in Africa for the 2009 [[Pirelli Calendar]] by [[Peter Beard]]. In 2009, she became the face of [[Dolce & Gabbana]] and Givenchy Spring/Summer 2009 ad campaigns. She was the face of the Fall/Winter 2009 [[Salvatore Ferragamo]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]] and Dolce & Gabbana ad campaigns.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n\nIn 2011 she was photographed by [[Steven Meisel]] for [[Prada]]'s spring collection and returned to fashion shows for [[Roberto Cavalli]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.paperblog.com/mariacarla-boscono-x-roberto-cavalli-inverno-2012-la-campagna-472592/|title=Mariacarla Boscono X Roberto Cavalli Inverno 2012 \u2013 La Campagna|website=Paperblog|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.italianstylekuwait.com/2010/11/mariacarla-boscono-by-steven-meisel/|title=Italian Style in Kuwait {{!}} Mariacarla Boscono by Steven Meisel|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In the same year she became the testimonial of [[Givenchy]]'s \"Dahlia Noir\" perfume.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.grazia.it/bellezza/profumi/givenchy-dahlia-noir|title=Givenchy Dahlia Noir: il nuovo profumo haute couture - Grazia.it|date=2012-09-03|website=Grazia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Boscono was also invited with [[Riccardo Tisci]] at [[Met Gala]]. In 2012 she is called for [[Missoni]]'s spring campaign,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://r1ma.blogspot.com/2012/04/mariacarla-boscono-for-missoni-spring.html|title=\u2665\u2665\u2665 Mariacarla Boscono for Missoni Spring 2012 full Ad Campaign by Juergen Teller|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> while in 2013 she walked in [[Armani]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.fashionnetwork.com/news/Mariacarla-boscono-nella-nuova-campagna-giorgio-armani,334531.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono nella nuova campagna Giorgio Armani|last=IT|first=FashionNetwork com|website=FashionNetwork.com|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> [[Alberta Ferretti]] and [[Dior]]'s runways.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashiontimes.it/2013/07/mariacarla-boscono-per-alberta-ferretti/|title=Mariacarla Boscono per Alberta Ferretti|date=2013-07-09|website=Fashion Times|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashionblog.it/post/114967/dior-presenta-la-nuova-collezione-autunno-inverno-2013-2014|title=Dior presenta la nuova collezione autunno-inverno 2013-2014|date=2013-07-26|website=Fashionblog.it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> From 2014 to 2015 she became the new model for [[Salvatore Ferragamo]] and came back to [[Alberta Ferretti]]'s runway. In 2014 she was photographed by [[Mert and Marcus]] for spring session by [[Armani]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.fashionnetwork.com/news/Mariacarla-boscono-nella-nuova-campagna-giorgio-armani,334531.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono nella nuova campagna Giorgio Armani|last=IT|first=FashionNetwork com|website=FashionNetwork.com|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 Boscono is hired for the Fall/Winter collection for [[Chanel]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chanel.com/it_IT/moda/news/2016/07/fall-winter-2016-17-pre-collection.html|title=PRE-COLLEZIONE AUTUNNO-INVERNO 2016/17|last=CHANEL|website=CHANEL|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[Mugler]] and spring campaign of [[Stella McCartney]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilgazzettino.it/moda/stella_mccartney_sceglie_natalia_vodianova_mariacarla_boscono_estate_2016-1580865.html|title=Mariacarla Boscono new entry per Stella McCartney|website=www.ilgazzettino.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[La Perla (clothing)|La Perla]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fashioneditorials.com/mariacarla-boscono-and-natasha-poly-by-mert-alas-marcus-piggott/|title=LA PERLA S/S 2016 - Mariacarla Boscono and Natasha Poly by Mert Alas & Marcus Piggott|date=2016-01-06|website=Fashion Editorials|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> and [[Redken]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/beauty-features/redken-mariacarla-boscono-new-face-10338416/|title=Redken Taps Mariacarla Boscono|last=Weil|first=Jennifer|last2=Weil|first2=Jennifer|date=2016-02-03|website=WWD|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2017 she becomes the face of [[Bottega Veneta]], [[Vera Wang]] and [[Oscar de la Renta]]'s Fall/Winter campaigns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwebradio.fm/oscar-de-la-renta-sara-mariacarla-boscono-il-volto-della-campagna-autunno-inverno-2017-2018/|title=Oscar de la Renta: sar\u00e0 Mariacarla Boscono il volto della campagna autunno inverno 2017-2018|date=2017-08-24|website=iWebRadio - Emozioni Senza Confini !!!|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2018 she appeared in [[Equipment (clothing brand)|Equipment]] collection,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voila.life/moda/mariacarla-boscono-2018-equipment/|title=Mariacarla Boscono \u00e8 protagonista della campagna 2018 di Equipment|last=Chimera|first=Patrizia|date=2018-02-27|website=Voil\u00e0 Magazine|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> [[Ermanno Scervino]] winter collection photographed by [[Peter Lindbergh]], and the new luxury collection by [[Marc Jacobs]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/foto-gallery/moda/news/17_giugno_09/ermanno-scervino-profumo-donna-mariacarla-boscono-cara-delevingne-brigitte-macron-2350f7c8-4d18-11e7-a0c3-52aebd58a53d.shtml|title=Ermanno Scervino, profumo di donna tra Mariacarla Boscono, Cara Delevingne e Brigitte Macron|date=2017-09-06|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/it/star/a25785299/mariacarla-boscono-chi-e-modella-italiana/|title=Mariacarla Boscono, la top model magnetica che ama il no-underwear e la perdita di controllo|last=Adorno|first=Di Mary|date=2019-01-08|website=Cosmopolitan|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> In 2019 [[Paris Fashion Week]] she walks on chat-way for [[Valentino (fashion designer)|Valentino]] and she was the guest model for [[Karl Lagerfeld]]<nowiki/>x[[Luisa Via Roma|LuisaViaRoma]]'s for the 90\u00b0 anniversary of the boutique.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amica.it/gallery/luisaviaroma-la-sfilata-evento-per-90-anni-della-boutique/?item=86|title=LuisaViaRoma: la sfilata-evento per i 90 anni della boutique Foto 86|website=Amica|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zimbio.com/photos/Mariacarla+Boscono/Valentino+Runway+Paris+Fashion+Week+Haute/EORInagUc6x|title=Mariacarla Boscono Photos Photos: Valentino : Runway - Paris Fashion Week - Haute Couture Fall/Winter 2019/2020|website=Zimbio|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> Boscono mada a campaign for [[Burberry]] in [[Korea]] and participated at [[Met Gala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fashiongonerogue.com/editorial/mariacarla-boscono-burberry-vogue-korea-cover/|title=Mariacarla Boscono Charms in Burberry for Vogue Korea|date=2019-01-28|website=Fashion Gone Rogue|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/article/met-gala-2019-mariacarla-boscono-camp-burberry-riccardo-tisci|title=Met Gala 2019: Mariacarla Boscono incarna il Camp indossando Burberry|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In 2020 she is the new face for [[Zara (retailer)|Zara]]'s summer collection,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/moda/gallery/zara-campagna-primavera-estate-2020-mariacarla-boscono|title=Zara: Mariacarla Boscono testimonial della knitwear primavera estate 2020|website=Vogue Italia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> the model for [[Daniel Lee (designer)|Daniel Lee]]'s collection for [[Bottega Veneta]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mffashion.com/news/backstage/daniel-lee-presenta-la-nuova-collezione-di-bottega-veneta-201906131227048464|title=Daniel Lee's collection 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> she walks the runway of [[Tod's]], [[Versace]], [[Burberry]], [[Salvatore Ferragamo]], [[Tom Ford]] Fall/Winter collections. Boscono walked also [[Valentino (fashion designer)|Valentino]]'s runway and posed for his spring campaign by [[Juergen Teller]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zimbio.com/photos/Mariacarla+Boscono/Tod+Runway+Milan+Fashion+Week+Fall+Winter/hfsbCtQYNAX|title=Mariacarla Boscono Photos Photos: Tod's - Runway - Milan Fashion Week Fall/Winter 2020-2021|website=Zimbio|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n== Theatre career ==\nOn 18 May 2006, Boscono made her theater debut as Solange in [[Jean Genet]]'s ''The Maids'' at the [[Lee Strasberg]] Theatre Institute in New York. [[Margherita Missoni]] played the role of her sister.<ref>{{cite journal|journal=The Daily Mini|last=Krentcil|first=Faran|title=Maid of Honor|date=July 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/fashion/models/mboscono/mariacarlaboscono/|website=New York Magazine|accessdate=23 August 2014|title=Model Profile \u2013 Mariacarla Boscono}}</ref> In 2010she played the role of Florizer in Imogen Kusch's ''Shakespeare's Women'' at [[Colosseum]] in [[Rome]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.it/magazine/people-in-vogue/2010/03/mariacarla-in-vogue|title=Mariacarla Boscono - Vogue.it|website=www.vogue.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> while in 2011 she acted in ''The Winter's Tale'' and ''[[Cymbeline]]'', both by Imogen Kusch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.klesidra.org/project/king-cymbeline/|title=King Cymbeline \u2013 Klesidra|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://the-style-post.blogspot.com/2011/02/mariacarla-boscono-all-for-shakespeare.html|title=The Style Post: Mariacarla Boscono, \"I'm all for Shakespeare '|last=G|first=Ernesto|date=2011-02-19|website=The Style Post|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn August 2012, Mariacarla announced the birth of her daughter, Marialucas.<ref>Alex Rees, [http://nymag.com/thecut/2012/08/mariacarla-boscono-gave-birth.html# And Just Like That, Mariacarla Boscono Gave Birth\"], ''New York Magazine'', August 2012</ref> She is a single mother.<ref>Faran Krentcil, [http://www.elle.com/fashion/interviews/a32452/mariacarla-boscono-interview/ \"Mariacarla Boscono on Modeling, Motherhood and Mac n' Cheese\"], ''Elle'', December 2015</ref> Boscono is living in New York, and calls it her second home, coming second after her birthplace of Rome.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n\nSince 2019 she is into a relationshio with tirteen younger italian rapper [[Ghali (rapper)|Ghali]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/sette/incontri/20_febbraio_14/ghali-ecco-chi-sono-io-radici-arabe-italiane-milano-mia-casa-fdaf7756-4b6b-11ea-aff7-4a3600894a18.shtml|title=Ghali: \"Fino all\u2019anno scorso dormivo con mamma. Mariacarla? Mi ama anche se la carriera finisce\"|last=Proietti|first=Andrea Laffranchi e Michela|date=2020-02-14|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\n== Agencies ==\n* Women New York\n* Women Milan (Mother Agency)\n* Women Paris<ref>[http://www.womenmanagement.fr/model/2563/mariacarla-boscono/''Women Paris'']</ref>\n\n== Clothing brands and magazine covers ==\n\n=== Clothing brands ===\n\n* [[Alberta Ferretti]] (1997-2000, 2013-2015)\n*[[Alessandro Dell'Acqua]] (1998-2001)\n*[[Armani]] (2000-2001, 2013-2015)\n* [[Bottega Veneta]] (2017-present)\n*[[Bulgari]] (2010\n*[[Burberry]] (2019-present)\n*[[Calvin Klein (company)|Calvin Klein]] (2000-2003)\n*[[Chanel]] (1997-present)\n* Coccinelle<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailyonline.it/it/2016/coccinelle-va-online-con-la-top-mariacarla-boscono-per-la-collezione-pe|title=Coccinelle va online con la top Mariacarla Boscono per la collezione P/E|website=www.dailyonline.it|language=it|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> (2016)\n*[[Comme des Gar\u00e7ons]] (1999-2000)\n* [[Dior]] (2008-2009, 2013-2014)\n* [[Dolce & Gabbana]] (2000-2009)\n* [[DSquared2]] (2016-present)\n* [[Emilio Pucci]] (2008)\n*[[Equipment (clothing brand)|Equipment]] (2018)\n*[[Ermanno Scervino]] (2017-2018)\n*[[Escada]] (2003-2004)\n*[[Fausto Sarli]] (1997-2000)\n* [[Fendi]] (2008)\n*Gai Mattiolo (1997-1998)\n*[[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]] (2000-2009)\n*[[Givenchy]] (2000-present)\n* [[Gucci]] (2008, 2016)\n*[[Guy Laroche]] (1997-present)\n*[[H&M]] (2005-2006)\n* [[Herm\u00e8s]] (2008)\n*[[Issey Miyake]] (1997)\n* [[Jean-Paul Gaultier]] (2008)\n* [[John Galliano]] (2008)\n* [[La Perla (